<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.191403>
    bibo:endPage "50" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "35" ;
    bibo:volume "2291" ;
    dc:creator "Zhao, Zeng Qi" ;
    dc:date "2009" ;
    dc:title "New Zealand species of the genus Tripyla Bastian, 1865 (Nematoda: Triplonchida: Tripylidae). I: A new species, a new record and key to long-tailed species" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.191404>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.191406>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.191410>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.191411>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.191407> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.191404>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1 Tripyla bioblitz sp. nov. A: Female, entire. B: Pharyngeal region, lateral. C: Head, lateral. D: Sub-female head, lateral. E: Genital region, lateral. F: Ventral view of cross section through vagina. G: Female tail. H: Spinneret. I: En face view of female. Scale bars: A, B, E, G = 50 μm; C, D = 25 μm. F, H = 10 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/191404/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.191406>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2 Tripyla bioblitz sp. nov. Photomicrographs. A: Female pharyngeal region, lateral. B: Amphid (arrowed). C: En face view. D: Spinneret. E: Cardia region (arrowed). F: Genital region, vulva, lateral. G: Anus & caudal glands (arrows indicate glands). Scale bars = 10 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/191406/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.191410>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5 Bayesian phylogenetic tree inferred from SSU gene DNA sequences. Posterior probabilities great than 50 % are given on appropriate clades. Nematode species, GenBank numbers, locations are listed for each taxon if known." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/191410/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.191411>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6 Bayesian phylogenetic tree inferred from LSU gene DNA sequences. Posterior probabilities greater than 50 % are given on appropriate clades. Nematode species, GenBank numbers, locations are listed for each taxon if known." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/191411/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.191407>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3 Tripyla filicaudata. A: Female entire, lateral. B: Male entire, lateral. C: Female head, lateral. D: Sub-female head, lateral. E: Genital region, lateral. F: Female tail. G: Spinneret. H: Male genital region. Scale bars: A, B, E, F, H = 50 μm; C, D = 25 μm. G = 10 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/191407/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

